The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The scoring scheme proposed in the paper is used to select samples from the target domain, which is a common technique in deep learning and computer vision. The paper also discusses the use of pseudo-labels, which is a common technique in semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
